org.jamsim.ascape.navigator

Class OutputNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ascape.model.event.DefaultScapeListener
      • org.jamsim.ascape.navigator.OutputNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, EventListener, ScapeListener, HasName

    public class OutputNode
extends DefaultScapeListener
    A ScapeListener that displays Navigator output nodes after each iteration and/or at the end of the simulation. Nodes displayed are provided by a OutputNodeProvider.
    Version:
    $Revision$
    Author:
    Oliver Mannion

        public void addOutputNode(DefaultMutableTreeNode node,
                 int runNumber)
        Add node to appropriate run sub folder.
        Parameters:
        node - node to add
        runNumber - the run number subfolder under which to create the child node. If the run number is SubFolderNode.ALLRUNS, then it is created under the "All Runs" node.
